## ğŸ”§ Development

### Project Structure

```
BioShield-Integration/
â”œâ”€â”€ adaptive/              # Adaptive intelligence
â”œâ”€â”€ orchestrator/          # Cascade management
â”œâ”€â”€ modules/               # Level wrappers
â”œâ”€â”€ config/                # Configuration files
â”œâ”€â”€ tests/                 # Unit tests
â”œâ”€â”€ data/                  # Runtime data
â”œâ”€â”€ reports/               # Generated reports
â”œâ”€â”€ logs/                  # System logs
â”œâ”€â”€ requirements.txt
â”œâ”€â”€ setup.py
â””â”€â”€ README.md
```

### Adding a New Module

1. Create wrapper in `modules/your_module/`
2. Implement standard interface
3. Register in `cascade_manager.py`
4. Add config section in `integration_config.yaml`

### Contributing

1. Fork the repository
2. Create feature branch (`git checkout -b feature/amazing-feature`)
3. Commit changes (`git commit -m 'Add amazing feature'`)
4. Push to branch (`git push origin feature/amazing-feature`)
5. Open Pull Request

